That was the LA1816. I can&#39;t get the AM oscillator to run very well 
above 4 MHZ, I&#39;ve had that problem on all the Japanese chips. 
So...today I started yet another proto type board using the old 
LM3820 AM only chip. I&#39;ve had those up to 20mhz easy, I didn&#39;t use 
them in any boxes though because they don&#39;t have a built in detector, 
and they were AM only. I have over 70 of the LM3820&#39;s that I paid 12 
cents each for. 

 Frank-S

